{
  "image": "6710\\6710.jpg",
  "title": "Romeo & Juliet's Notebook",
  "description": "Two households, both alike in dignity, in fair Strathcona where we lay our scene. Join Romeo Yellowhead and Juliet Henday, star-crossed lovers from different sides of town in an all new parody musical mashup from Spotlight Cabaret at The Garneau Theatre! This tragic romance is packed with passion, puns and pop hits.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Aimée Beaudoin and Jeff Halaby<br/><strong>Director</strong>: John Hudson<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Aimée Beaudoin, Jeff Halaby, Tyler Pinsent, Abby Vandenberghe<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Aaron Macri<br/>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "In Strathcona, two teens from very different families fall in love. Romeo Yellowhead and Juliet Henday must fight against their families, friends, and the world just to be together. Their story is told through a notebook Romeo keeps for Juliet, filled with memories of their love. Romeo &amp; Juliet’s Notebook is a fun and emotional musical parody with pop songs, mashups, and Spotlight Cabaret’s signature humour. Performed at the Garneau Theatre, this show is full of love, drama, and unforgettable moments.",
